adjectives.description: unservicelike (comparative more unservicelike, superlative most unservicelike)

entries.meaning: Not characteristic of the naval service; unseamanlike.
examples: The mate's unservicelike style of acquiescence — "With much pleasure sir," rather surprised, if it did not actually disconcert our 'gallant post,' who for a few seconds stared at him with all his eyes, open mouthed to boot,  […]
